definitions.definition: A banknote with a value of five units of currency.
examples: Do you have a fiver I could borrow? I can pay you back tomorrow.

definitions.definition: The value in money that this represents.
examples: I bought the chocolates; they were only a fiver .

definitions.definition: A mathematical puzzle played on a 5 × 5 grid.
A Zaydi Shiite Muslim, who disagrees with the majority of Shiites on the identity of the Fifth Imam.
A person who gives five percent of their income or five hours a week of their time to charity (a reduction of ten percent tithing ).
